<section xml:id="C4.S6">
<title>Power Series</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C4.S6.SS1">
<title>Logarithms</title>          
<para xml:id="C4.S6.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C4.S6.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.6.1" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E1">\ln\left(1+z\right)=z-\tfrac{1}{2}z^{2}+\tfrac{1}{3}z^{3}-\cdots, if |z|\leq 1, z\neq-1,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.6.2" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E2">\ln z=\left(\frac{z-1}{z}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{z-1}{z}\right)^{2}+ \frac{1}{3}\left(\frac{z-1}{z}\right)^{3}+\cdots, if \Re z\geq\frac{1}{2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.6.3" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E3">\ln z=(z-1)-\tfrac{1}{2}(z-1)^{2}+\tfrac{1}{3}(z-1)^{3}-\cdots, if |z-1|\leq 1, z\neq 0,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.6.4" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E4">\ln z=2\left(\left(\frac{z-1}{z+1}\right)+\frac{1}{3}\left(\frac{z-1}{z+1} \right)^{3}+\frac{1}{5}\left(\frac{z-1}{z+1}\right)^{5}+\cdots\right), if \Re z\geq 0, z\neq 0,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.6.5" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E5">\ln\left(\frac{z+1}{z-1}\right)=2\left(\frac{1}{z}+\frac{1}{3z^{3}}+\frac{1}{5 z^{5}}+\cdots\right), if |z|\geq 1, z\neq\pm 1,</Math> 
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C4.S6.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C4.S6.SS1.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.6.6" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E6">\ln\left(z+a\right)=\ln a+2\left(\left(\frac{z}{2a+z}\right)+\frac{1}{3}\left( \frac{z}{2a+z}\right)^{3}+\frac{1}{5}\left(\frac{z}{2a+z}\right)^{5}+\cdots \right), if a&gt;0, \Re z\geq-a, z\neq-a</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S6.SS2">
<title>Powers</title>         
<paragraph xml:id="C4.S6.Px1">
<title>Binomial Expansion</title>   
 
<para xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.6.7" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S6.E7">(1+z)^{a}=1+\frac{a}{1!}z+\frac{a(a-1)}{2!}z^{2}+\frac{a(a-1)(a-2)}{3!}z^{3}+\cdots</Math> , valid when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.m1">a</Math> is any real or complex constant and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.m2">|z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.s2">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.m3">a=0,1,2,\dots</Math> , then the series terminates and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S6.Px1.p1.m4">z</Math> is unrestricted. Note that (4.6.7) is a generalization of the binomial expansion (1.2.2) with the binomial coefficients defined in (1.2.6).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
